==Malayalam==
===Noun===
'''അച്ഛന് ''' (atʃtʃhan)
#[[father]]
====Declension====

=====Singular=====

* '''Nominative''': അച്ഛന്     ''atʃtʃhan'' 
* '''Vocative''': അച്ഛാ        ''atʃtʃhaː''
* '''Accusative''': അച്ഛനെ    ''atʃtʃhane'' 
* '''Dative''': അച്ഛന്         ''atʃtʃhan(u)'' 
* '''Genitive''': അച്ഛന്റ്റെ     ''atʃtʃhante''
* '''Locative''': അച്ഛനില്      ''atʃtʃhanil''

=====Plural=====
* '''Nominative''': അച്ഛന്മാര്        ''atʃtʃhanmaːr'' 
* '''Vocative''': അച്ഛന്മാരേ         ''atʃtʃhanmaːreː'' (long é) 
* '''Accusative''': അച്ഛന്മാരെ       ''atʃtʃhanmaare'' 
* '''Dative''': അച്ഛന്മാര്ക്ക്           ''atʃtʃhanmaːrkk(u)'' 
* '''Genitive''': അച്ഛന്മാരുടെ        ''atʃtʃhanmaːruʈe'' 
* '''Locative''': അച്ഛന്മാരില്         ''atʃtʃhanmaːril''

====Synonyms====

* പിതാവ്     ''pitaːʋ(u)''    This word was derived from Sanskrit ''pitar'' and is considered very formal.
* തന്ത       ''tanta''      This is a very colloquial and rude term meaning father.
* ബാപ്പ        ''baːppa''        This is the word that most muslims who speak malayalam use for father.

